<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>ResearchNest - Case Study | Derek Muriuki</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.0.0-beta3/css/all.min.css">
    <style>
        /* Case Study Specific Styles */
        .case-study {
            max-width: 1200px;
            margin: 0 auto;
            padding: 2rem;
            color: var(--text);
        }
        
        .case-header {
            text-align: center;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            position: relative;
            padding-bottom: 2rem;
        }
        
        .case-header::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translateX(-50%);
            width: 100px;
            height: 3px;
            background: var(--neon-blue);
        }
        
        .case-hero {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            gap: 2rem;
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
        }
        
        .case-hero-image {
            width: 100%;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 10px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }
        
        .case-hero-image:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
        }
        
        .case-meta {
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            gap: 2rem;
            margin: 1rem 0;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
        }
        
        .meta-item {
            display: flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            background: rgba(100, 181, 246, 0.1);
            padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
            border-radius: 20px;
            font-size: 0.9rem;
        }
        
        .meta-item i {
            color: var(--neon-blue);
        }
        
        .case-section {
            margin-bottom: 3rem;
            background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.03);
            padding: 2rem;
            border-radius: 10px;
            border-left: 3px solid var(--neon-blue);
        }
        
        .case-section h2 {
            color: var(--neon-blue);
            margin-top: 0;
            margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
            position: relative;
            padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
        }
        
        .case-section h2::after {
            content: '';
            position: absolute;
            bottom: 0;
            left: 0;
            width: 50px;
            height: 2px;
            background: var(--neon-blue);
        }
        
        .case-image {
            width: 100%;
            border-radius: 8px;
            margin: 1.5rem 0;
            box-shadow: 0 5px 15px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        
        .case-features {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
            gap: 1.5rem;
            margin: 2rem 0;
        }
        
        .feature-card {
            background: rgba(100, 181, 246, 0.05);
            padding: 1.5rem;
            border-radius: 8px;
            border: 1px solid rgba(100, 181, 246, 0.1);
            transition: transform 0.3s ease, box-shadow 0.3s ease;
        }
        
        .feature-card:hover {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        
        .feature-card i {
            font-size: 1.5rem;
            color: var(--neon-blue);
            margin-bottom: 1rem;
            display: inline-block;
        }
        
        .case-cta {
            text-align: center;
            margin: 3rem 0;
        }
        
        .btn-case {
            display: inline-flex;
            align-items: center;
            gap: 0.5rem;
            padding: 0.8rem 2rem;
            background: var(--neon-blue);
            color: #fff;
            text-decoration: none;
            border-radius: 50px;
            font-weight: 500;
            transition: all 0.3s ease;
            margin: 0 0.5rem 1rem;
        }
        
        .btn-case:hover {
            background: transparent;
            border: 1px solid var(--neon-blue);
            color: var(--neon-blue);
            transform: translateY(-2px);
        }
        
        .btn-case i {
            transition: transform 0.3s ease;
        }
        
        .btn-case:hover i {
            transform: translateX(5px);
        }
        
        .btn-outline {
            background: transparent;
            border: 1px solid var(--neon-blue);
            color: var(--neon-blue);
        }
        
        .btn-outline:hover {
            background: var(--neon-blue);
            color: #fff;
        }
        
        @media (max-width: 768px) {
            .case-hero {
                flex-direction: column;
            }
            
            .case-meta {
                flex-direction: column;
                align-items: center;
                gap: 1rem;
            }
            
            .case-section {
                padding: 1.5rem;
            }
        }
        
        body {
            font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
            background: #f9f9f9;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 0;
            line-height: 1.6;
            color: #333;
        }

        .container {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            background: white;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0,0,0,0.05);
        }

        h1, h2, h3 {
            color: #222;
        }

        h1 {
            font-size: 2em;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        h2 {
            border-bottom: 2px solid #ddd;
            padding-bottom: 5px;
            margin-top: 30px;
        }

        table {
            width: 100%;
            border-collapse: collapse;
            margin-top: 10px;
        }

        th, td {
            padding: 10px;
            text-align: left;
            border-bottom: 1px solid #eee;
        }

        .badge {
            background: #007acc;
            color: white;
            padding: 4px 8px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            font-size: 0.85em;
            margin-right: 5px;
        }


    a {
      color: #007acc;
      text-decoration: none;
    }

    a:hover {
      text-decoration: underline;
    }

    ul {
      margin-top: 10px;
    }

    .footer-links {
      margin-top: 20px;
      padding-top: 10px;
      border-top: 1px solid #eee;
    }

    .footer-links a {
      display: inline-block;
      margin-right: 15px;
    }

    .keywords span {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #eee;
      padding: 3px 8px;
      margin: 3px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      font-size: 0.85em;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="container">
    <h1>🎓 Student Research Archive + Analytics</h1>
    <p><strong>Type:</strong> Full-stack Flask Web App &nbsp;|&nbsp; <strong>Stack:</strong> Flask · HTML · CSS · Bash · Linux</p>

    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>
      A web-based archive system that allows students to upload PDF research papers. Metadata is automatically extracted (title, authors, keywords), with search and filtering features. Admins can track research trends using a built-in analytics dashboard.
    </p>

    <h2>Problem</h2>
    <p>
      Institutions often lack a searchable, centralized archive of student research. Academic efforts are lost, trends go unnoticed, and paper access becomes tedious.
    </p>

    <h2>Solution</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Secure student upload of PDF research papers</li>
      <li>Automatic extraction of metadata and keyword tagging</li>
      <li>Search and filter by department, year, keywords</li>
      <li>Admin dashboard showing download trends and topic heatmaps</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Key Features</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Feature</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Authentication</td><td>Separate login for students and admins</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Metadata Extraction</td><td>Title, authors, keywords pulled from PDFs using Python</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Virus Scanning</td><td>ClamAV integrated for secure uploads</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Search/Filter</td><td>Search by department, year, or keywords</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Analytics</td><td>Admin sees download counts, popular topics, activity by department</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Tech Stack</h2>
    <p>
      <span class="badge">Flask</span>
      <span class="badge">HTML/CSS</span>
      <span class="badge">SQLAlchemy</span>
      <span class="badge">PyMuPDF</span>
      <span class="badge">RAKE</span>
      <span class="badge">Bash</span>
      <span class="badge">Linux</span>
    </p>

    <h2>Challenges & Solutions</h2>
    <table>
      <tr><th>Challenge</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Inconsistent PDF metadata</td><td>Fallback to content parsing using NLP on abstract section</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Upload security</td><td>Integrated ClamAV scanning in Bash scripts</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Slow large-file processing</td><td>File size limit + plan to add async in future</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Results</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Uploads with metadata extraction working at ~85% accuracy</li>
      <li>Clear admin dashboard with visual trends</li>
      <li>Secure file uploads with virus scanning</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Lessons Learned</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>PDF metadata is unreliable – always plan for fallback extraction</li>
      <li>Flask is powerful but needs more boilerplate than Django</li>
      <li>Good UX and helpful error messages greatly improve user trust</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Future Plans</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>PDF preview using PDF.js</li>
      <li>AI-based paper recommendations</li>
      <li>Export data to Excel</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="footer-links">
      <strong>Links:</strong><br />
      🔗 <a href="#">GitHub Repo</a>  
      🌐 <a href="#">Live Demo</a>  
      📄 <a href="#">Sample PDF Upload</a>  
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
